*Description*

Fix upcomng deliveries for users who's subscribed SKU is not matching the upcoming/future deliveries SKU

Background:
When user subscribes to a new SKU via "cadence change" flow, we patch their subscription, but not meal selection (its cadence change, so meals are the same - no need to patch it). Unfortunately in such scenario BE still holds stale SKU meal selections scheduled.The way we handle this gap in the frontend is, we re-select meals on new SKU on users behalf (regardless if its a cadence change or other reason), so that box content service always gets propagated with the new SKU selections. We patched this partially a ~week after after 10th of December (when this user has been affected). There is still one cadence touchpoint to patch in settings, we will address this asap, and going forward there should be no issue.
{panel}

